log.4president.org/2020/2019/06/trump-campaign-announces-launch-of-latinos-for-trump-ahead-of-the-2020-election-.html|title=Trump Campaign Announces Launch of 'Latinos for Trump' Ahead of the 2020 Election|work=2020 Presidential Campaign Blog|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[George P. Bush]], [[Texas General Land Office|Land Commissioner]] of [[Texas]] 2015\u2013present<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/card/george-p-bush-sticks-trump-rocky-reelection-bid-n853641 |title=George P. Bush sticks with Trump in re-election bid |work=[[NBC News]] |date=March 5, 2018 |accessdate=April 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Former====\n* [[Adam Putnam]], [[Florida Commissioner of Agriculture|Commissioner of Agriculture]] of [[Florida]] 2011\u20132019; [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] from [[Florida's 12th congressional district|FL-12]] 2001\u20132011; candidate for [[List of Governors of Florida|Governor]] in [[2018 Florida gubernatorial election|2018]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/florida-politics/buzz/2018/06/28/and-the-winner-of-desantis-vs-putnam-debate-trump/|title=And the winner of DeSantis vs. Putnam debate? Trump!|date=June 28, 2018|first1=Adam C.|first2=Steve|last1=Smith|last2=Contorno|work=[[The Tampa Bay Times]]|accessdate=June 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===State Senators===\n====Current====\n*[[Ryan Fattman]], [[Massachusetts State Senate|State Senator]] from [[Massachusetts]] (Worcester and Norfolk district) 2015\u2013present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natick.wickedlocal.com/news/20200229/political-notebook-mass-sees-73-increase-in-registered-voters-since-16|title=POLITICAL NOTEBOOK: Mass. sees 7.3% increase in registered voters since '16|first=Daily News Staff and News|last=Services|website=Natick Bulletin and Tab}}</ref>\n*[[Mike Testa]], [[New Jersey State Senate|State Senator]] from [[New Jersey's 1st Legislative District]] 2019\u2013present<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.courierpostonline.com/story/news/local/south-jersey/2020/01/28/nj-sen-mike-testa-speak-wildwood-trump-re-election-rally/4601050002/|title=State Sen. Testa speaks ahead of Trump, Van Drew at Wildwood rally|website=Courier-Post}}</ref>\n*[[Chris A. Brown]] State Senator from the [[2nd Legislative District (New Jersey)]] 2018\u2013present<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n*[[Christopher J. Connors]] State Senator from the [[9th Legislative District (New Jersey)]] 2008\u2013present<ref name=\"auto4\">{{Cite web|url=https://savejersey.com/2020/01/road-work-route-47-trump-rally-murphy-wildwood/|title=LD1 legislators ask NJDOT to delay roadwork ahead of Trump's Wildwood rally \u00bb|date=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Kristin Phillips-Hill]] State Senator from the [[Pennsylvania Senate, District 28]] 2019\u2013present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yorkdispatch.com/story/news/2019/12/10/sen-kristin-phillips-hill-speak-trump-rally-hershey/4388598002/|title=Sen. Kristin Phillips-Hill to speak at Trump rally in Hershey|first=Lindsey|last=O'Laughlin|website=York Dispatch}}</ref>\n* [[Ralph Alvarado]], Member of the [[Kentucky State Senate]] from the 28th district 2015\u2013present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/11/04/donald-trump-rallies-matt-bevin-tight-kentucky-election/4155302002/|title=At Kentucky rally, Donald Trump claims 'far left' is trying to impose 'authoritarian ideology' on nation|first=Michael|last=Collins|website=USA TODAY}}</ref>\n\n===State legislators===\n====Current====\n* [[Alonzo Baldonado]], [[New Mexico House of Representatives|State Representative]] from [[New Mexico]] (District 8) 2011\u2013present<ref name=ltndt/>\n* [[Antwan McClellan]], Member of the [[New Jersey General Assembly]] from [[New Jersey's 1st Legislative District]] 2020\u2013present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsbreak.com/new-jersey/wildwood/news/0NyRLdE5/mcclellan-thrilled-to-have-trump-in-wildwood|title=McClellan Thrilled to have Trump in Wildwood &#124; News 