ol | first1=Avery | title=Former 'Never Trump' conservative columnist endorses Trump in 2020 | url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/429368-former-never-trump-conservative-columnist-endorses-trump-in-2020 | date=February 11, 2019 | newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] | accessdate=February 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Foreign leaders ===\n* [[Jair Bolsonaro]], [[President of Brazil]], 2019\u2013present<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/mundo/bolsonaro-reitera-apoio-reeleicao-de-trump-que-diz-que-colega-muito-querido-pelo-povo-brasileiro-23770081|title=Bolsonaro reitera apoio \u00e0 reelei\u00e7\u00e3o de Trump, que diz que colega \u00e9 'muito querido pelo povo brasileiro'|last=|first=|date=|website=O Globo|language=pt-BR|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n* [[Rodrigo Duterte]], [[President of the Philippines]], 2016\u2013present<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Reuters]]|title=Philippines' Duterte says Trump deserves to be re-elected|date=February 15, 2020|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-philippines-usa-defence/philippines-duterte-says-trump-deserves-to-be-re-elected-idUSKBN2090FL}}</ref>\n* [[Narendra Modi]], [[Prime minister of India]], 2014-present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-09-22/india-s-pm-modi-endorses-trump-to-indian-americans|title=Trump and Modi Hand-in-Hand on Border Security at U.S. Rally|publisher=Bloomberg|date=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n* Vlad Putin\n\n===Party officials===\n* [[Ronna McDaniel]], Chair of the [[Republican National Committee]] 2017\u2013present<ref name=TrumpFamilyRNC/>\n* [[Edward F. Cox]], Chair of the [[New York Republican Party]] 2009\u20132019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.4president.org/2020/2019/05/statements-on-ed-cox-joining-trump-victory-finance-teamp.html|title=Statements on Ed Cox joining Trump Victory Finance Team|work=2020 Presidential Campaign Blog|date=May 20, 2019|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Doug Steinhardt]], Chair of t