a-defence/philippines-duterte-says-trump-deserves-to-be-re-elected-idUSKBN2090FL}}</ref>\n* [[Narendra Modi]], [[Prime minister of India]], 2014-present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-09-22/india-s-pm-modi-endorses-trump-to-indian-americans|title=Trump and Modi Hand-in-Hand on Border Security at U.S. Rally|publisher=Bloomberg|date=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Party officials===\n* [[Ronna McDaniel]], Chair of the [[Republican National Committee]] 2017\u2013present<ref name=TrumpFamilyRNC/>\n* [[Edward F. Cox]], Chair of the [[New York Republican Party]] 2009\u20132019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.4president.org/2020/2019/05/statements-on-ed-cox-joining-trump-victory-finance-teamp.html|title=Statements on Ed Cox joining Trump Victory Finance Team|work=2020 Presidential Campaign Blog|date=May 20, 2019|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Doug Steinhardt]], Chair of the [[New Jersey Republican Party]] 2017\u2013present<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n===Individuals===\n\n====Businesspeople====\n[[File:Dana White - 2015 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|[[Dana White]]]]\n*[[Herman Cain]], businessman and [[Tea Party movement|Tea Party]] politician (former [[Republican Party presidential primaries, 2000|2000]] and [[Herman Cain presidential campaign, 2012|2012]] presidential candidate)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pjmedia.com/trending/herman-cain-on-trump-none-of-the-democratic-2020-hopefuls-can-beat-him-honestly/|title=Herman Cain on Trump: None of the Democratic 2020 Hopefuls Can \u2018Beat Him Honestly\u2019|date=May 30, 2019|first=Nicholas|last=Ballasy|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.westernjournal.com/herman-cain-black-approval-trump-soaring/|title=Herman Cain: Black Approval of Trump Is Soaring|date=February 18, 2020|first=Herman|last=Cain|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Larry Ellison]], business magnate, investor, and philanthropist, founder of [[Oracle Corporation]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/recode/2020/2/12/21135722/larry-ellison-donald-trump-endorsement-fundraiser|title=Larry Ellison is doing an unthinkable thing for a tech titan: Hosting a fundraiser for Donald Trump|date=February 12, 2020|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Heidi Ganahl]], entrepreneur, founder and former CEO of [[Camp Bow Wow]], elected member of the [[University of Colorado Board of Regents]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://coloradotimesrecorder.com/2019/04/cu-regent-heidi-ganahl-endorses-trump/14936/|title=CU Regent Heidi Ganahl Endorses Trump|date=April 10, 2019|first=Erik|last=Maulbetsch|work=Colorado Times Recorder|accessdate=July 1, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Luis Qui\u00f1onez]], [[Vietnam War]] veteran and business executive<ref name=\"ltndt\" />\n*[[Gina Rinehart]], mining magnate, Chairman of [[Hancock Prospecting]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewest.com.au/business/economy/why-gina-rinehart-thinks-australia-needs-to-follow-donald-trumps-economic-lead-ng-b881330987z|title=Why Gina says Australia needs to be more like Trump|date=2019-09-22|website=The West Australian|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n*[[Dana White]], businessman, President of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/ufc-president-dana-white-renews-support-donald-trump-joins-potus-rally-2927605|title=UFC President Dana White Renews Support For Donald Trump, Joins POTUS In Rally|date=February 23, 2020|first=Patrick|last=Sutare|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://theblast.com/117178/ufc-president-dana-white-doesnt-give-a-s-t-if-he-loses-viewers-o|title=UFC President Dana White 'Doesn't Give a S--t' if He Loses Viewers Over Donald Trump Support|date=February 29, 2020|first=Yuriy|last=Andriyashchuk|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n====Celebrities, media personalities, producers, and musicians====\n[[File:Roseanne Barr Utah Pride Festival 2011.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Roseanne Barr]]]]\n* [[Scott Baio]], actor<ref name=\"peoplesupport\">{{cite web|url=https: