<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/Maroon5VEVO/about|title=Maroon5VEVO| work=YouTube| accessdate=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| {{Flag|USA}}\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 49.\n|\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0637\u064a\u0648\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0646\u0629 | toyoraljanahtv<ref name=\"toyoraljanahtv\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/toyoraljanahtv/about|title=toyoraljanahtv|website=YouTube|access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ceecf2\" |N/A\n| {{Flag|JOR}}\n| [[Arabic]]\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 50.\n| FunToys Collector Disney Toys Review<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/DisneyCollectorBR/about|title=FunToys Collector Disney Toys Review| work=YouTube| accessdate=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| Entertainment\n| {{Flag|USA}}\n| [[English language|English]] \n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:8pt;\" | As of {{date|April 20,2020|mdy}} UTC\n|}\n\n==Historical progression of most-viewed channels==\nThe first-created and first-viewed [[YouTuber|YouTube channel]] was \"Jawed\" created on April 23, 2005 by YouTube co-founder [[Jawed Karim]].<ref name=\"jawed1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC4QobU6STFB0P71PMvOGN5A|title=jawed|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref><ref name=\"jawed2\">{{Cite web|url=https://citizenevidence.amnestyusa.org|title=Extract Meta Data|website=citizenevidence.amnestyusa.org|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref> The first YouTube channel to exceed 10{{nbsp}}billion views was [[PewDiePie]] in September 2015. Since then, 93{{nbsp}}channels have exceeded 10{{nbsp}}billion views as of November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/top/100/mostviewed|title=Top 100 most viewed YouTube channels}}</ref>\n\n[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] became the most-viewed YouTube channel of 2016,<ref name=\"Ha\">{{cite book |last=Ha |first=Louisa |title=The Audience and Business of YouTube and Online Videos |date=2018 |publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield]] |isbn=9781498576499 |page=154 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UoNaDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA154}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Former Presidents and stars come together to bid epic farewell to Queen of Soul, Aretha Franklin |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/former-presidents-and-stars-come-together-to-bid-epic-farewell-to-queen-of-soul-aretha-franklin/articleshow/65631083.cms |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=September 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bollywood Supports T-Series Music {{!}} The World Most Viewed Channel On YouTube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CkFqXIPYNYY |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=T-Series |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |date=February 3, 2017}}</ref> and exceeded 14{{nbsp}}billion views by January 2017.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Laghate |first1=Gaurav |last2=Sachitanand |first2=Rahul |title=How Bhushan Kumar has transformed T-Series into an entertainment behemoth |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/how-bhushan-kumar-has-transformed-t-series-into-an-entertainment-behemoth/articleshow/57048309.cms |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=February 9, 2017}}</ref> It eventually surpassed PewDiePie to become the most-viewed YouTube channel of all time by February 16, 2017,<ref name=\"feb2017\">{{cite web |title=Top 100 YouTubers sorted by Most Viewed |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216095230/socialblade.com/youtube/top/100/mostviewed |website=Social Blade |accessdate=February 16, 2017}}</ref> and currently maintains the lead with over 102+ billion views overall. T-Series has also had the most monthly views since 2016,<ref>{{cite news |title=Top 100 Most Viewed YouTube Channels Worldwide \u2022 December 2016 |url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/01/19/top-100-most-viewed-youtube-channels-worldwide-december-2016/ |work=[[Tubefilter]] |date=January 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=YouTube: most viewed channels 2018 |url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/373729/most-viewed-youtube-channels/ |website=[[Statista]] |date=June 2018 |accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref> and currently receives over 2.8{{nbsp}}billion views per month as of May 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=T-Series YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics |url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/c/tseriesmusic |website=Social Blade |accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nMusic is the most-viewed program genre on YouTube, across the globe.<ref name=\"Ha\"/> By 2016, the most-viewed YouTube channels were [[record label]]s (e.g. T-Series), [[YouTuber]]s (e.g. [[Ryan ToysReview]]), music stars (e.g. [[Justin Bieber]]), and nursery videos (e.g. [[Little Baby Bum]]).<ref>{{cite book |last=Anabela |first=Mesquita |title=Research Paradigms and Contemporary Perspectives on Human-Technology Interaction |date=2017 |publisher=IGI Global |isbn=9781522518693 |page=44 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hYIJDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA44}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Resources |first1=Management Association, Information |title=Sports Media, Marketing, and Management: Breakthroughs in Research and Practice: Breakthroughs in Research and Practice |date=2018 |publisher=IGI Global |isbn=9781522554769 |page=63 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_Q9MDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA63}}</ref>\n\nThe following table lists the channels that became YouTube's most-viewed channel at different points in time.\n\n{{legend|#d0f0c0|Current record for most days as most-viewed channel}}{{legend|#d7ccf3|Former record for most days as most-viewed channel}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Channel name\n! Network / owner\n! data-sort-type=\"usLongDate\" | Date achieved\n! Days held\n!Views\n! Reference\n! Country\n|-\n| [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]<ref name=\"T-Series\"/>\n| [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| align=right | February 16, 2017\n| style=\"background:#d0f0c0; text-align:center;\" | '''{{age in days|2017|2|16}}'''\n|14.6 billion\n| align=center | <ref name=\"feb2017\"/>\n| {{Flag|IND}}\n|-\n| [[PewDiePie]]<ref name=\"PewDiePie\" />\n| [[Felix Kjellberg]]\n| align=right | December 29, 2014\n| style=\"background:#d7ccf3; text-align:center;\" | '''{{age in days|2014|12|29|2017|2|16}}'''\n|7.7 billion\n| align=center | <ref name=SB-emimusicarchive>{{cite web |url=http://socialblade.com/youtube/user/emimusic |title=emimusic YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics (27 December 2014\u20135 January 2015 archive) |work=[[Social Blade]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105214309/http://socialblade.com/youtube/user/emimusic|archive-date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=31 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=SB-PDParchive-2014>{{cite web |url=http://socialblade.com/youtube/user/pewdiepie |title=PewDiePie YouTube Stats, Channel Statistics (23 December 2014\u20131 January 2015 archive) |work=[[Social Blade]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102021934/http://socialblade.com/youtube/user/pewdiepie|archive-date=2 January 2015 |accessdate=31 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Top 100 YouTubers sorted by Most Viewed |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102021835/socialblade.com/youtube/top/100/mostviewed |website=Social Blade |accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref>\n| {{Flag|SWE}}\n|-\n| [[EMI Music Publishing|EMI Music]]<ref>{{cite web |title=emimusic |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/emimusic |website=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n| [[EMI Music Publishing|EMI Music]]\n| align=right | June 15, 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{age in days|2014|6|15|2014|12|29}}\n|6.2 billion\n| align=center | <ref>{{cite web |title=Top 100 YouTubers sorted by Most Viewed |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140615003701/socialblade.com/youtube/top/100/mostviewed |website=Social Blade |accessdate=December 22, 2014}}</ref>\n| {{Flag|GBR}}\n|-\n| [[Rihanna|RihannaVEVO]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Rihanna VEVO|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/RihannaVEVO|website=YouTube|publisher=[[Roc Nation]]|accessdate=April 2, 2018}}</ref>\n| [[Rihanna]]\n| align=righ